      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Amoud Foundation's financial health is a primary differentiator. With an <cite id=\"14\">overall score of 88.88.5/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>, the organization demonstrates high accountability. Their <cite id=\"5\">fundraising efficiency of $0.00 per $1 raised</cite> is a rare metric in the humanitarian sector, indicating that nearly every dollar donated is utilized for service delivery rather than donor acquisition. This is supported by a <cite id=\"15\">perfect 100/100 Leadership score</cite>, reflecting strong organizational management."
      ],
      "summary": "founded in 1998, the Amoud Foundation has established itself as a cornerstone of humanitarian relief in the Horn of Africa, specifically focusing on <cite id=\"1\">Somaliland, Somalia, Ethiopia, and Djibouti</cite>. The organization operates with a lean financial model, reporting <cite id=\"2\">$9,535,194 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year. Their mission centers on providing assistance to <cite id=\"3\">15 orphan centers and two schools for the deaf and blind</cite>, addressing critical gaps in social services for the most vulnerable. Amoud maintains a highly efficient operation, directing <cite id=\"4\">89.3% of its expenses toward core programs</cite> according to recent filings. This efficiency is further highlighted by a <cite id=\"5\">fundraising efficiency of $0.00 per $1 raised</cite>, meaning the charity spends virtually nothing on marketing to generate its revenue. Beyond orphan care, the foundation manages diverse portfolios including <cite id=\"6\">water projects, emergency food aid, and healthcare services</cite>. Their long-standing presence in the region for over <cite id=\"7\">25 years</cite> allows them to navigate complex local environments to deliver direct aid. The organization is <cite id=\"8\">Zakat-eligible</cite>, providing a verified pathway for Muslim donors to fulfill their religious obligations through programs that serve the <cite id=\"9\">poor (fuqara) and needy (masakin)</cite>.",
